rror handling rules**\\n\\nI need to look at the guideline that says to catch errors, verify them, and then rethrow if they don’t match. This means I should swallow any unsupported errors. It looks like the existing CodegenTest is already following this approach, which is good. I want to make sure I’m aligning with that rule in my work, so I’ll focus on consistent error handling in my coding practices.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering class structure and tests**\\n\\nI’m thinking about whether the context is still active. Maybe I should split the tests into a separate class? Having an active class test in its own dedicated file might be a good idea. I also need to address any compile warnings since I've noticed that System.getSecurityManager tests are deprecated, but that shouldn't cause any issues. I’ll go ahead and add the new file for clarity.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_EnQ6kXEH1oK5gduQMtjBSG09|fc_04005c52923d8a13016a2756ccb15c81969e9669d6a2a6b3d3", "name": "write", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/org.mozilla/rhino/1.7R5/src/test/java/org_mozilla/rhino/ToolsShellMainTest.java", "content": "/*\n * Copyright and related rights waived via CC0\n *\n * You should have received a copy of the CC0 legalcode along with this\n * work. If not, see <http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/>.\n */\npackage org_mozilla.rhino;\n\nimport static org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThat;\n\nimport java.io.IOException;\nimport java.io.OutputStream;\nimport java.io.PrintStream;\nimport java.nio.file.Files;\nimport java.nio.file.Path;\n\nimport org.graalvm.internal.tck.NativeImageSupport;\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\nimport org.mozilla.javascript.CompilerEnvirons;\nimport org.mozilla.javascript.Context;\nimport org.mozilla.javascript.Scriptable;\nimport org.mozilla.javascript.SecurityController;\nimport org.mozilla.javascript.optimizer.ClassCompiler;\nimport org.mozilla.javascript.tools.shell.Main;\n\npublic class ToolsShellMainTest {\n    @Test\n    void mainInitializesJavaPolicySecuritySupportWhenRequested() {\n        String previousSecurityProperty = System.getProperty(\"rhino.use_java_policy_security\");\n        PrintStream previousOut = Main.getOut();\n        PrintStream previousErr = Main.getErr();\n        try (PrintStream ignoredOutput = new PrintStream(OutputStream.nullOutputStream())) {\n            System.setProperty(\"rhino.use_java_policy_security\", \"true\");\n            Main.setOut(ignoredOutput);\n            Main.setErr(ignoredOutput);\n\n            Main.main(new String[] {\"-e\", \"var initializedByPolicySecurity = true;\"});\n\n            assertThat(SecurityController.hasGlobal()).isTrue();\n        } finally {\n            restoreSystemProperty(\"rhino.use_java_policy_security\", previousSecurityProperty);\n            Main.setOut(previousOut);\n            Main.setErr(previousErr);\n        }\n    }\n\n    @Test\n    void processFileExecutesCompiledScriptClass() throws IOException {\n        try {\n            Path compiledScript = compileScriptClass(\n                    \"ShellCompiledScript\",\n                    \"var shellCompiledScriptValue = 42;\");\n\n            Context context = Context.enter();\n            try {\n                Scriptable scope = context.initStandardObjects();\n\n                Main.processFile(context, scope, compiledScript.toString());\n\n                assertThat(Context.toNumber(scope.get(\"shellCompiledScriptValue\", scope)))\n                        .isEqualTo(42.0d);\n            } finally {\n                Context.exit();\n                Files.deleteIfExists(compiledScript);\n            }\n        } catch (Error error) {\n            if (!NativeImageSupport.isUnsupportedFeatureError(error)) {\n                throw error;\n            }\n        }\n    }\n\n    private static Path compileScriptClass(String className, String source) throws IOException {\n        Context context = Context.enter();\n        try {\n            CompilerEnvirons compilerEnvirons = new CompilerEnvirons();\n            compilerEnvirons.initFromContext(context);\n            ClassCompiler compiler = new ClassCompiler(compilerEnvirons);\n            Object[] compiledClasses = compiler.compileToClassFiles(source, className + \".js\", 1, className);\n            byte[] mainClassBytes = (byte[]) compiledClasses[1];\n            Path classFile = Files.createTempDirectory(\"rhino-shell-main-test\")\n                    .resolve(className + \".class\");\n            Files.write(classFile, mainClassBytes);\n            return classFile;\n        } finally {\n            Context.exit();\n        }\n    }\n\n    private static void restoreSystemProperty(String key, String previousValue) {\n        if (previousValue == null) {\n            System.clearProperty(key);\n        } else {\n            System.setProperty(key, previousValue);\n        }\n    }\n}\n"}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 932, "output": 1950, "cacheRead": 27648, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 30530, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1780962995734, "responseId": "resp_04005c52923d8a13016a2756b4427081968dc21689ce6d2dd9"}, "toolResults": [{"role": "toolResult", "toolCallId": "call_EnQ6kXEH1oK5gduQMtjBSG09|fc_04005c52923d8a13016a2756ccb15c81969e9669d6a2a6b3d3", "toolName": "write", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Successfully wrote 3653 bytes to tests/src/org.mozilla/rhino/1.7R5/src/test/java/org_mozilla/rhino/ToolsShellMainTest.java"}], "isError": false, "timestamp": 1780963027654}]}
